
Overview of noun stoic

The noun stoic has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) Stoic -- (a member of the ancient Greek school of philosophy founded by Zeno; "a Stoic achieves happiness by submission to destiny")
2. (1) stoic, unemotional person -- (someone who is seemingly indifferent to emotions)

Overview of adj stoic

The adj stoic has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (3) stoic, stoical -- (seeming unaffected by pleasure or pain; impassive; "stoic courage"; "stoic patience"; "a stoical sufferer")
2. Stoic -- (pertaining to Stoicism or its followers)
